nodes.bodyText:
We could also use Optional's to reduce the cognitive complexity here. Something like this
Optional<JsonObject> errorsOptional = Optional.ofNullable(responseContent)
    .filter(json -> json.has("errors"))
    .map(json -> json.get("errors").getAsJsonObject());
Optional<JsonElement> errorsReporterOptional = errorsOptional
    .filter(errorsJson -> errorsJson.has("reporter"))
    .map(errorsJson -> errorsJson.get("reporter"));
if (errorsReporterOptional.isPresent()) {
    throwReporterException(errorsReporterOptional.get(), issueCreatorEmail);
}
The optionals should help reduce the nested if's when dealing with the JsonObjects.

